INSERT INTO `game` (`id`, `url`, `name`, `name_vn`, `short_desc`, `long_desc`, `order_weight`, `is_promote`, `is_fearture`, `link_youtube`, `is_active`) VALUES
(1, 'bomberman-hudson-soft-1987-nitendo', 'bomberman hudson soft 1987 nitendo', 'game đặt bom', 'Bomberman is a robot engaged in the production of bombs. Like his fellow robots, he had been put to work in an underground compound by evil forces. Bomberman  found it to be an unbearably dreary existence.', '<h2 dir="ltr"><span>Game story</span></h2>\n<p dir="ltr"><span style="font-size: medium;">Bomberman is a robot engaged in the production of bombs. Like his fellow robots, he had been put to work in an underground compound by evil forces. Bomberman &nbsp;found it to be an unbearably dreary existence. One day, he heard an encouraging rumor. According to the rumor, any robot that could escape the underground compound and make it to the surface could become human . Bomberman leaped at the opportunity , but escape proved to be no small task. Alerted to Bomberman betrayal, large numbers of the enemy set out in pursuit. Bomberman can only rely on bombs of his own production for his defense. Will he ever make it up to the surface? Once there, will he really become human?</span></p>\n<p><span><span>&nbsp;</span></span></p>\n<h2 dir="ltr"><span>Control function </span></h2>\n<p dir="ltr"><span style="font-size: medium;">left/right/up/down move the Bomberman to left/right/up/down</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span style="font-size: medium;">A button to lays down a bom</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span style="font-size: medium;">B button is used when you pick up the remote controlling explosion panel </span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span><img style="display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;" src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/45zfXBB1txP6Aj40PVWGneP9n644En4eMgXe9Wav7Bh37Uz9AFjtjhFgVt2x_7lTLYnO9dnnt5AaQ8zDSHzLs1Sv3OHjLVXlw7L-Wi5wyffiaNiRaUOOscNQjz_t_F-vf11xgl54" alt="" width="467" height="145" /></span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Select button : when title screen appears, choose start or continue. Make your choice by pressing select button</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Start button : if you press start the game will start if start is selected, the game will start anew from screen 1, if continue is selected the game will progress from the last screen of most recently played game. A game can be temporarily halted by press the start button. to start the game simple pressing the start button again.</span></p>\n<p><span><span>&nbsp;</span></span></p>\n<h2 dir="ltr"><span>How to play game</span></h2>\n<p dir="ltr"><span style="font-size: medium;">Bomberman''s goals is to reach the surface of the earth. However, hist initial point of departure &nbsp;is deep in bowel of the earth, so Bomberman must search for exitways and make his way upwards, level by level. Of course, enemy forces are lurking throughout the labyrinth, and Bomberman must overcome each and everyone in order to advance to the next level. If he should touch any of the enemy or be caught in the fames of exploding bombs, also concealed in brick wall are power up panels, which bomberman collects in order to increase his power. </span></p>\n<h3 dir="ltr"><span>Bombs: </span></h3>\n<p dir="ltr"><span style="font-size: medium;">In the earliest stage of the game, only one bomb can be set at a time and it has very weak fire power. As power-up panels a taken in, the boms become easier to use and more lethal.</span></p>\n<h3 dir="ltr"><span>Bricks</span></h3>\n<p dir="ltr"><span style="font-size: medium;">These dissolve when hit by the flames of exploding bombs. Hidden within the bricks are exitways and power-up panels, so it is wise to bomb out as many bricks as possible</span></p>\n<h3 dir="ltr"><span>Concrete</span></h3>\n<p dir="ltr"><span style="font-size: medium;">Concrete walls aren''t damaged by bomb fires, so bomberman can take shelter from exploding bombs. </span></p>\n<p><span><span>&nbsp;</span></span></p>\n<h3 dir="ltr"><span>Exitway</span></h3>\n<p dir="ltr"><span style="font-size: medium;">There are to be found among the bricks. after overcoming all enemies, Bomberman stands over &nbsp;the exitways to proceed to the next level. However, Bomberman is in real trouble if an exitway is hit by a bomb.</span></p>\n<p><span><span>&nbsp;</span></span></p>\n<h3 dir="ltr"><span>Power-up panels</span></h3>\n<p dir="ltr"><span style="font-size: medium;">These panels turn up &nbsp;occasionally among the bricks. there are several different types of panels with different effects. For example, in the illustration below, a panel is shown that has a picture of a bomb. When this panel is picked up, the number of boms can be set at one time. The picture seen on the panels show their various effects. There are levels that can not be cleared if bomberman does not collect a large number of power-up panels, so panels should be pickup whenever they are found.</span></p>\n<p><span><span>&nbsp;</span></span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span><img style="display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;" src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/senYQ9dARAkOXYLWOAvnHzEMLKbruaXxeVTAQ9vDHkDrRaRskOjaCy149F8flM9Mn7UDVtmnvc14DKCnXl_xXyCPKzOIOzCRz8ROJQqUyRkNmybh-9tNJ3oVzV4ewR7vGXwzUT91" alt="" width="431" height="113" /></span></p>\n<p><span><span>&nbsp;</span></span></p>\n<h3 dir="ltr"><span>Enemy characters</span></h3>\n<p dir="ltr"><span style="font-size: medium;">There are 8 types of enemy characters. Each type moves in its own particular fashion, so it''s wise to learn their moves. If all enemies on a single level can be knocked out by 7 bombs, a player''s score will increase greatly.</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span><img style="display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;" src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/nDVYglhYkf4BVT5N24H06k4qAdc2H30EIJX6Wl0TsAhIJAkGwqis4kgWFdb7JTrmjbzd-fFxtstfJ3_oZXY4v-RUo-MNbwq2MdqUlzAktAHziW8HBMda-EB0gcWftD1USCM_EE7x" alt="" width="480" height="163" /></span></p>\n<p><span><span>&nbsp;</span></span></p>\n<h3 dir="ltr"><span>Bonus level</span></h3>\n<p dir="ltr"><span style="font-size: medium;">A bonus level is awarded after the consective five levels are cleared. The objective on bonus level is to take out as many enemies as possible within a limit time. On these levels, Bomberman can''t be hurt by exploding bombs, so dump the explosives as much as you can.</span></p>\n<h3 dir="ltr"><span>Note</span></h3>\n<p dir="ltr"><span style="font-size: medium;">Exploding bombs may cause temporary discoloration of blocks on screen or cause screen to fuzzy momentarily. These temporary ocurrances have no effect on game progress</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span style="font-size: medium;">during the course of a game, players may discover new technics, hidden characters, and other features not covered in this manual. These are part of the challenge of this game and it''s up to the player to work them out. gook luck! &nbsp;&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p><span><span>&nbsp;</span></span></p>\n<p dir="ltr">&nbsp;</p>\n<p><span id="docs-internal-guid-ffe0b43b-8684-b645-74ca-23c433eca0c6"><br /><br /></span></p>', 0, 0, 0, 'https://www.youtube.com/embed/3smytj9Bu_E?ecver=1', 1),
(2, 'lode-runner-hudson-1983-1984-nitendo', 'lode runner hudson 1983 1984 nitendo', 'lode runner', 'you are the galactic commando deep in enemy territory . power hungry leaders of the repressive Bungleing Empire have stolen for a fortune in gold  from the . Your task? to infiltrate each of 50 different treasury rooms, evade the deadly Bungeling guards, and recovery every stack of Bungeling booty', '<h2 dir="ltr"><span>game description</span></h2>\n<p><span><span>&nbsp;</span></span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>you are the galactic commando deep in enemy territory . power hungry leaders of the repressive Bungleing Empire have stolen for a fortune in gold &nbsp;from the . Your task? to infiltrate each of 50 different treasury rooms, evade the deadly Bungeling guards, and recovery every stack of Bungeling booty</span></p>\n<p><span><span>&nbsp;</span></span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>controlling lode runner</span></p>\n<p><span><span>&nbsp;</span></span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>controller 1 for 1 player game</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>controller 2 for second player in 2 player game</span></p>\n<p><span><span>&nbsp;</span></span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span><img style="display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;" src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/DLodTuilBALbjik7xbTGKWJ9f5dN_kiUMeNxk4rwGmrbkjc8DKVVke846TbpbnHzNuXFNLA8_gQ5qO1rGHmYa2yfS_dvl2jOSLHBx70-DunjNt52PPEwWCcHv2cOovOMGlaSxibf" alt="" width="331" height="336" /></span></p>\n<ul>\n<li dir="ltr">\n<p dir="ltr"><span>A button drills a hole on the right side of the Lode Runner </span></p>\n</li>\n<li dir="ltr">\n<p dir="ltr"><span>B button drills a hole on the left side of the Lode Runner </span></p>\n</li>\n<li dir="ltr">\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Up button climb up ladder</span></p>\n</li>\n<li dir="ltr">\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Down button climb down ladder of jump off hand-bar</span></p>\n</li>\n<li dir="ltr">\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Left button move left</span></p>\n</li>\n<li dir="ltr">\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Right button move right</span></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><span><span>&nbsp;</span></span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span><img style="display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;" src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/XGd3z_36Ze5QtD4THlxaO1XwJx4CElt5zseYRFUC5qJX2jSqTP6vSSFf-DZFJ0bJ2j7IQVxf9jeGBcR2D5oDEXm7ToqcPxNtUv7-5DcVI0xeIFvoT97EWFi0sd5QQDtH94pAADa-" alt="" width="410" height="246" /></span></p>\n<p><span><span><br /><br /><br /><br /></span></span></p>\n<h2 dir="ltr"><span>Playing the game</span></h2>\n<p dir="ltr"><span><img style="display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;" src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/7I_z4jKN7iMmrSIW_j8HrKgTnXw1qWX4jiqQM6t5QT3auOZS7eHlJV0d-xH4rRQVHrTUASRU35hxGlTraSHeYbIIwD_fWbKhTBucCun3Qxtriwv0lSc_wowBMV85MaU_oadTGzhR" alt="" width="409" height="185" /></span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span><img style="display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;" src="https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/V78hZsQsmfqg2XbX0gO3NWs2rbizTknXDmX-t19E8MyW8VyB77RTCdG8fImWKu1VgWWXmL-loCPhktnNUp8o9li-x0Vu7BIe5c_fzknmjLox5rVofwYDIa9R_cx5I-hN_4XFHn9c" alt="" width="413" height="490" /></span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span> To complete a level you must collect all the gold in a level. When you succeed you may then climb a ladder to the top of the screen and enter the next level. You will use your laser drill pistol tho drill pits and passageways through brick floors. You may dig through fissured bricks only not through solid surfaces and holes must be drilled all the way through to be effective. If the title screen is left on for 30s the program automatically begins a self-playing demo . watch to get a sense of game play.</span></p>\n<p><span><span>&nbsp;</span></span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Trapping the Bungelings (or yourself)</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>If a bungeling guard falls into a pit and get stuck, it will become safe (for a moment) for you to run over him; also he will release any gold he is carrying. Any holes that you&lsquo;ve drilled will fill in again after a period of time, and guards caught in them when they refill will die and be replenished by new guards at top of screen</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Be careful! Guard can climb out of bits that do not close up around them. Your player , however, cannot climb out of pits and will die if trapped in a pit with a floor that is only a single brick wide.</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>You will notice that gold carried by a Bungeling cease to be visible. If you have picked up all the visible gold on the screen and the ladder leading to the next level has not yet appeared or you cannot reach the next level by climbing to the highest part of the screen, one or more of the guards is still carrying gole. You must trap the guards in a pit and picked up their gold</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>If an enemy carrying gold falls into a *dead end* and you cannot dig him , you will not be able to get that gold. If either you or a Bungeling &nbsp;with gold get stuck in a *dead end*, press select to the level selection screen and restart the level.</span></p>\n<p><span><span><br /><br /></span></span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Scrolling screen</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>The Lode Runner screen is a large rectangle left to right. For that reason , all you see on the TV screen is about half of the entire level</span></p>\n<ul>\n<li dir="ltr">\n<p dir="ltr"><span>When you move the screen will scroll to the lode runner</span></p>\n</li>\n<li dir="ltr">\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Whatever appears on the screen is about half of the level when you can&rsquo;t find golde or an escape ladder , search for it by moving the Lode Runner around the screen - there must be one somewhere</span></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><span><span>&nbsp;</span></span></p>\n<h2 dir="ltr"><span>Score</span></h2>\n<ul>\n<li dir="ltr">\n<p dir="ltr"><span>When you escape from a level your score will be displayed and you will receive an extra Lode Runner (maximum 9 runner)</span></p>\n</li>\n<li dir="ltr">\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Gold 100 points</span></p>\n</li>\n<li dir="ltr">\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Robot 100 points</span></p>\n</li>\n<li dir="ltr">\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Once in awhile a fruit appears you get bonus points if you can catch the fruit</span></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>High score is displayed before each new level, however by pressing the reset button or turning off the machine you will lose your high score</span></p>\n<p><span><span>&nbsp;</span></span></p>\n<h2 dir="ltr"><span>Technique</span></h2>\n<p><span><span>&nbsp;</span></span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Lode Runner can jump from any height he can even jump off of a hand-bar or ladder or through a hole in the floor</span></p>\n<p><span><span>&nbsp;</span></span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span><img style="display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;" src="https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/-ctBzKCExVHQSUB7WHvO2eceLt8pe-jQgk9kILIecKHu5BzzQmTsZ8BVsM7lt0XauGhNorTXaoKjt_8nXZaPoMtE9T9_5VDULAHPui9CLUSn085lksBFHfvSTKPWky48874lRFrw" alt="" width="198" height="188" /></span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>The only place that you can dig a hole is in a fissured brick, however there are a couple of other places that you cannot dig a hole such as directly underneath a ladder, directly underneath a hand-bar or in a trap door</span></p>\n<p><span><span>&nbsp;</span></span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>The Lod Runner can dig a hole to jump to but if the hole is no more than one brick wide and there is a bottom to the hole , he will not able to climb out</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span><img style="display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;" src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/RrRbCSNJ-DGpJ8vkvF5b7wDfo4NbLdPc-E3jnzkUGxGnJXqqBiRh-_PpxXKa1npXmhrH9_LKN5VjDDINmqkHQfmexUZqjf686PP1l-rPMazqC0su2MTTTlHg84CrDcgF_iSMHxB7" alt="" width="198" height="81" /></span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Getting the gold</span></p>\n<p><span><span>&nbsp;</span></span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span><img style="display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;" src="https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/YsS53Vw5Z66quMOC-2VmYTM9qp3BB51YYJFgRdedpnsoUBalrRDGM3zIU4Z0tHs-U9qIIC3l-efOTpu2KCyAOenf6apszXjMx79GOicCOr_ajv42YT4556gk8tUkSHRoAftjytDh" alt="" width="211" height="478" /></span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>By running through a stack of gold you can pick it up. If it&rsquo;s floating in the middle of the air you can drop on the gold to pick it up. If the gold is surrounded by bricks, dig a hole . in order to dig a hole there must be at least two spaces 9 one to stand on and one to dig), so plan carefully how to get buried gold also, don&rsquo;t forget to dig a hole so &nbsp;you can escape. If you collect all the gold but escape ladder not appear remember, Bungelings sometimes carry gold. In this case, dig a hole to trap the Bungeling &nbsp;and if it has any gold it will drop it.</span></p>\n<p><span><span>&nbsp;</span></span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Finding the escape ladder</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>The ladder reaching to the top of the screen is the escape ladder. if you collect all the golds, music will play and the escape ladder will appear. when you climb up this ladder , you can go to the next level. there are &nbsp;50 levels, how many levels can you complete?</span></p>\n<p><span><span><br /><br /></span></span></p>\n<h2 dir="ltr"><span>Design your own game boards</span></h2>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>To use the editor</span></p>\n<ul>\n<li dir="ltr">\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Press the reset button to get to the title screen</span></p>\n</li>\n<li dir="ltr">\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Use the select button to move to edit mode</span></p>\n</li>\n<li dir="ltr">\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Press start button and you will see the editing screen (as show in the diagram). Now you are ready to edit your own screen</span></p>\n</li>\n<li dir="ltr">\n<p dir="ltr"><span>To quit editing, press select and start button at the same time to bring you back to the title screen</span></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>You may only create one screen at a time. Any screen you design will be lost if you press the reset button or turn off the power to machine</span></p>\n<p><span><span>&nbsp;</span></span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Placing the lode runner shapes</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>The process of designing your own broads is simple. Place gold, bricks or ladders anywhere you like on the screen to create your own level to play. there is one limitation - the screen you can create is only the size of the tv monitor, so it doesn''t scroll.</span></p>\n<p><span><span>&nbsp;</span></span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span><img style="display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto;" src="https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/Z9SAECtheWoXNJEfTwRunho98Basg7xDT3kStbAJ-1-I0f6AkrCnDnRRtmQXLCJ0DuBh4U_Wx5lH8iIjpbSTCnQEQuvTT-wmDl2GIrr7tDaEWLlasKlaqOk3toGXYaKuZN58OHif" alt="" width="229" height="180" /></span></p>\n<ul>\n<li dir="ltr">\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Use the control pad to move the cursor (the blinking yellow square) up down left and right to place where you would like to place the character</span></p>\n</li>\n<li dir="ltr">\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Choose the character you&rsquo;d like to place. By pressing the A button you can scroll up through the choices of squares to place. Pressing B button will scroll down through the choices</span></p>\n</li>\n<li dir="ltr">\n<p dir="ltr"><span>When you get the character you want to place, move your cursor and that character will be placed where the cursor was</span></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><span><span>&nbsp;</span></span></p>\n<h2 dir="ltr"><span> Character and their order of appearance</span></h2>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>When you play your level the trap door(#5) will appear just like digable bricks. #6 (escape ladder) will be invisible until you have collected all the gold.use #10 blank to erase a square</span></p>\n<p><span><span>&nbsp;</span></span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span><img src="https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/Hn98bGJefFDHtn0OAZop6bk9iEUT56Wc86wjK0JBVm_702G35voMy9GluigOrqUEa9c8-vX-dYFnscRhk2Q_bE4SLITU-OBC8oiaFqWt8iXc8DrDju6wbKWP_BMV-LkMfpU5hJ8L" alt="" width="295" height="277" /></span><span><img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/MaCAjZqFgDNf306wGzPm2DYhtLVVnZMxNwMGXxA7sY_7asMzOR03sivB5283OXG6-0k7eB-7oX2Bh3d7NJgKyAFzdqJOKhy78XzB_j5DeVCyxOnHlBEfUO9NC_1V2Pcy0ftoG5T4" alt="" width="295" height="456" /></span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span><img src="https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/7bGiuGHSvujjCo7RO0YkXXVrAy7I2SAQ1_T1F_nEQGQzjt1bq14Rik1-pEqxbnAOWIaQVQ4vyR2ZQqTb7bgDHlDNCEKufwGFxbNkbWPFEQ70IGe3wPAtqIl7iUvqb8G_YC-5H25A" alt="" width="288" height="194" /></span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Play your own screen</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>When you&lsquo;ve created a screen that you like, press the start button to begin the game. The first time you plat a level you have create, you may find many problems. Pressing the select button will return you to the edit screen</span></p>\n<p><span><span>&nbsp;</span></span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Check the following in order to create a playable level</span></p>\n<ul>\n<li dir="ltr">\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Are all the gold placed where they can be gotten?</span></p>\n</li>\n<li dir="ltr">\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Is there an escape ladder reaching to the top of the screen?</span></p>\n</li>\n<li dir="ltr">\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Is there a way to get to the escape ladder?</span></p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>In order to check these points, it may be a good idea to play without Bungelings</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>When you clear your own level you will be return to the editing screen</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>If a runner is caught by a robot or buried inside a brick you will be returned to the edit screen</span></p>\n<p><span>&nbsp;</span></p>', 0, 0, 0, 'https://www.youtube.com/embed/ovRanSrw5Xs?ecver=1', 1),
(3, 'elevator-action-taito-nintendo-gun', 'elevator action taito nintendo-gun', 'elevator action', 'As super-sleuth agent 17, code name Offo, you must came out from undercover to accept a top-secret mission. your country''s security is at stake. you must sneak through a heavily guarded, top security enemy defense building to steal secret government documents.', '<h2 dir="ltr"><span>The story</span></h2>\n<p dir="ltr"><span><img src="https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/FQMXEVnZihOdey-UXEnFaIvBis465WR7FxsTRNg1U86rx1c-xb5xIiFUdUc4T8EboD72NNRzUv0jWETfUvuji4QQdPeEl7v_04NJfuMUukeyk2DqVnKfD7fT0wlHZW8v9qOScbLj" alt="" width="326" height="477" /></span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>As super-sleuth agent 17, code name Offo, you must came out from undercover to accept a top-secret mission. your country''s security is at stake. you must sneak through a heavily guarded, top security enemy defense building to steal secret government documents. only well-planned strategies, bullet-dodging, quick on the draw accuracy and black belt karate prowess will allow you to success. if you fail, your government will deny any knowledge of you or of your assignment. gook luck!</span></p>\n<p><span><span>&nbsp;</span></span></p>\n<p dir="ltr">&nbsp;</p>\n<h2 dir="ltr"><span>How to play </span></h2>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>You must break into the building from the rooftop, make a way cautiously down through the floors by way of elevators and escalators and pick up all the files hidden behind the red doors. Then you must make it to getaway car in the garage below.</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Enemy agent, armed and lying in wait behind the blue doors, will try to ambush you. Your weapons are your pistol and powerful jump-kick. Shoot the lights out to create blackouts whenever possible for higher scoring.</span></p>\n<p><span><span>&nbsp;</span></span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span><img src="https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/sVKC2oGdSMnJ_FqhyLX5hQsYfy3dANyoUMJ0GxQ9vruONBOJlMjZWwnnESXJl34RI7Yv97Pwz8tlSBR-KbXAUpGlYR8cG44vFXlu3qj84TQ6Q1SDip4DvMraulxn813Skp8NLP7p" alt="" width="455" height="306" /></span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>To enter a red door, stan directly on a white square in front of the door</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>To use the escalator stand directly on a white square and push the control pad up or down</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Jump over elevator shaft</span></p>\n<p><span><span><br /><br /></span></span></p>\n<h2 dir="ltr"><span>How to operate </span></h2>\n<p dir="ltr"><span><img src="https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/MZOF_IVPv3u1WAzxMQJa5_FQCGHSvUBDbPI6zv0pAPL1-TVeUQdfM3PIPu-WlT_LvS2ghGHKuUJbGDIi5RH-PRec7z7GSzKJE9EWY5rX5nW81PuQYgvFoKFv71QPEwcuczgas3D0" alt="" width="444" height="284" /></span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>A button : spy (player) jumps</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>B button : spy shoots</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Left button : move left</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Right button : move right</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Up button : stand</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Down button : duck</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Select button : choose 1 or 2 player</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Start button : start to begin play after player selection</span></p>\n<p><span><span>&nbsp;</span></span></p>\n<h2 dir="ltr"><span>Nh&acirc;n vật </span></h2>\n<p dir="ltr"><span><img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/IYInFzGhINCbbn7vpevCvze28i4nhVP5_ObfARU4uZTNknq0_OXSXizLi4cV7vpWVw3fW3x4D6hV6HygWO9yfj7bOjxUPgZDmunIHK-bGIHY8VYGV-s-f5Vc5xp8H4OvAoR0J7yJ" alt="" width="116" height="117" /></span><span>spy</span></p>\n<p><span><span>&nbsp;</span></span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span><img src="https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/XHj-I690ky2BmYlL-BRrVp_DQ8hM9A0wmaug1moj7We-PX-hKEIQPPOM2tZbFsO_9y_A7LvaFpUOGPi3LFCNNzQCXLrTMoAz6MCRuEh-FdHOrPhAgd8UCXSyvOeFER7FDj0YHFD6" alt="" width="116" height="121" /></span><span>security guard </span></p>\n<p><span><span>&nbsp;</span></span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span><img src="https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/MssbwrRqFNwvIs98m7dEP9t1L7ZIAhvDSCREmmNYwGtW1FO3B5l3IVHf5S9t61RXapyYxDj-dj1866VQgDlMqjjLDtSG7U7CK1_ya3V_LZGCiIGzXp4TU-7yIDAW3zdfeRRb_wro" alt="" width="109" height="112" /></span><span>lamp</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span><img src="https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/uxG91mUVAJIqUjreXGIbu2mu4QEq0S8UiY1sHnETgZ6kUMB9WHVaD8A1iZVlw8Ckd-OwD_hKNy4GzKtxbWs1Y3GaHzeKsZgfEgCCfHPIPRXZ7DvZuKU7gBkRINDCyVecOXDT_oKj" alt="" width="110" height="119" /></span><span>getaway car</span></p>\n<p><span id="docs-internal-guid-3a7729b0-86a8-fe55-097e-751b7d36b00f"><br /><br /></span></p>', 0, 0, 0, 'https://www.youtube.com/embed/izRhnBuXGnY?ecver=1', 1),
(4, 'spy-hunter-sunsoft-nintendo-racing', 'spy hunter sunsoft nintendo racing', 'spy hunter', 'Pilot your vehicle through the track. Seek and destroy enemy agents who will use every means to wipe you out. You must avoid the road hazards and protect the friendly pedestrian vehicles.', '<h3 dir="ltr"><span>Your mission</span></h3>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Pilot your vehicle through the track. Seek and destroy enemy agents who will use every means to wipe you out. You must avoid the road hazards and protect the friendly pedestrian vehicles. There''s terror at every turn - tire slashers, torpedos, bomb dropping helicopters standing in your way of the most diabolical collection of enemy agents ever to hit a video screen. You have your skill and reflexes along with Smoke screens, oil slicks and heat seeking missiles to outmaneuver your opponents . One mistake and it''s all over. So strap yourself in, no need to check your ammo. You''ve got more than enough; and take the challenge.</span></p>\n<p><span><span>&nbsp;</span></span></p>\n<h3 dir="ltr"><span>Control functions</span></h3>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Up button : turbo accelerator</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Down button : brake </span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Select button : select preferred; type of weapons</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Start button : starts mission; call weapons van</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>B button: machine guns.</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>A button : active weapons</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Quickly select the type of weapon from your arsenal the depress A button to use weapon.</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Hint : heat-seeking missiles only destroy the enemy helicopters.</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Press A button on the player 2 control to pause action.</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span><img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/XOH2oYyxhJUKP51phecB3BAblqJYZj4_zktfl9Z1sO75AIeBY4RR9tsgbmOnJpXRAY9IwSgJGH1ok27lnFSdIXPed8fyuUQctZ1i637hcEIALKCqdlhYWn3eAHpf9ba4LY2rxZlM" alt="" width="593" height="306" /></span></p>\n<h3 dir="ltr"><span>How to play</span></h3>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>You will receive one extra racer if you score 10000 points before the timer in lower right corner counts down to zero. Thereafter an additional racer will be awarded every 30000 points. Up to 5 additional cars are available for extended play.</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Your car will turn into a speed boat when it enters the beat house located on the river bank. The speed boat will contain at the weapons that were available to the car at that time. No new weapons can be carried while in the river.</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Acquire weapons by driving into the rear of any weapons van with the ramp down.</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Your turbo racer will be disabled upon contact with a tire slasher or bomb, when hit point blank by gunman in the limo, when hitting a bomb crater, when you collide with another vehicle moving &nbsp;at a much different speed, or when you leave the shoulder.</span></p>\n<p><span><span>&nbsp;</span></span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Your speed boat will be disabled when be hit by a torpedo or bomb, hitting a barrel, collide with a boat going a different speed, or when leaving the river bank.</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>All enemy vehicles are blue except the helicopters. Available weapons are displayed in the upper left corner.</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Spy Hunter is a one-player game.</span></p>\n<p><span><span>&nbsp;</span></span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span><img src="https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/o5wRlHfTu3TZ6XElTjSsov2FdhG1CAH8i3kC5eIGPHPp6SiZix_8P8YttnJwroB6YNMja26PPXiAJoIVhkz5FHNuqcWh47BUqYuf8dSNLlTlKdCVTufAk5yOfq5Byog_Ocytq-Nc" alt="" width="597" height="243" /></span></p>\n<p><span><span><br /><br /></span></span></p>\n<h3 dir="ltr"><span>Your weapons</span></h3>\n<p dir="ltr"><span><img src="https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/9X5FrYYa6QEbXH1hiKSkROFtv736M4COfir-0pTxXtAbwS6CifRNYNJpkMT91U_k5_YJe0MOcWIVWiqD5dQjXAVTLC3NvpYARW3Cio7tf7buXgV7mnjCOLKRM7Z_5B3DotX0ahUC" alt="" width="255" height="390" /></span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Along with your machine guns, you have a choice of a few other devastating toys.</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>A</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>SMOKE SCREEN - Used to slow down any surface vehicle foolish enough to come up from behind.</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>B</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>DIL - Rear mounted mounted nozzle sprays a layer of</span><span> ol </span><span>on the read to eliminate any surface vehicle &nbsp;from behind your racer.</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>C</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>MISSILES - Heat-seeking missiles which destroy the enemy helicopters.</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>NOTE: ALL NON-ENEMY VEHICLES YOU KILL WILL DISABLE POINT SCORING MOMENTARILY.</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span><img src="https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/eWLs-vs_ChlZjAYw5IFjBHjsJUuxd7A2pRqP5c220i82LhN3_jDJyDd62KAuoGiPu1mK9XmDLcvNjWhGzYdsqcAQNLE3Jozw7ZjfSbicqjYiOgUny6sCl9NIVyY-jRUtfbRqEnDM" alt="" width="258" height="205" /></span></p>\n<p><span><span><br /><br /></span></span></p>\n<h3 dir="ltr"><span>Otaining waepons</span></h3>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Call weapons van with start button. Weapon vans are only available as you travel into a new territory.</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Align your turbo racer directly behind weapons van ramp and accelerate into val.</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>You racer will then be dropped on the side of the road to continue your mission.</span></p>\n<p><span><span>&nbsp;</span></span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Cruise Boats : cruise boats equipped with two front/rear torpedo tubes.</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span><img src="https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/TIjoVjsHtX0il_7lErpUVhaKvoiJ5gGmgqoMfrjLBtE2tnyDBQEX5s4E4YE9VSGtYbiFXE4mWZEtQ6UhXWhN6ni2bRW5KXSuI4IFsJXo1d2d2-h1uCSHAJ8M9ipLkZKalkN1CzMQ" alt="" width="302" height="203" /></span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Speed boats : speed boats dropping barrels that explode on contact.</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span><img src="https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/smSsAMNa1gH8em_DIlTpxtGZEnZTzwGZ0GMVpij8AkZWrkWckU2C15pwIpMoGtLWR89yhz2DPlBpOoCVZWMeJj9fBkN0YYieFbQChjGtp4BPahongF8mpLetjrehaIxQqp8an02m" alt="" width="244" height="133" /></span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Helicopters : enemy helicopters equipped with bombs.</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span><img src="https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/Dcnomk7pT7kcwnsKMzZlK1oFFovDAa_Fk81nEx33jzWTqZZwC9rvSlYBWKfaoZuzW0Rvqwsil-utHeFCVtkQqIXsexEDyi34DPld2FSfjMHz3GVioyogkNSxVmag726TbxSffc8D" alt="" width="211" height="146" /></span></p>\n<h3 dir="ltr"><span>Road hazards</span></h3>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>As you maneuver down the road at break-neck speed , destroying your enemy, you must remember the people you''re here to protect. The friendly vehicles make you job difficult because of their slow speed and unpredictable behavior . They are not hostile and should not be fired upon.</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Other hazards include ; ice on the road, water puddles on the road, crater in the road from bombs.</span></p>\n<p><span><span>&nbsp;</span></span></p>\n<h3 dir="ltr"><span>Destroying enemy vehicles</span></h3>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Your racer is equipped with two front mounted guns. They are capable of disabling all enemy agents except card equipped with bullet proof rear armor and the bombs dropping helicopters.</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Throughout the game additional weapons may be earned.</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span><img src="https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/G3hmB1B-AtUtWS6IqCqUqI3eUTqi4csNzKdj-PaMtDMvs98pdyK1LEbWafhPoImWb_CodT008S8_evNIBf99FRXU-CiWv7gut5JbcUps7YI3YP18bVIJ2voP3Aebg0hbwjHgSVIU" alt="" width="589" height="339" /></span></p>\n<h3 dir="ltr"><span>Helpful hints</span></h3>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>It is inadvisable to pass enemy agents on a straight road. Try to run them off the road or wait until there are curvers .</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Oil is one of the most effective ways of dealing with trailing enemy agent ground vehicles.</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>When coming to the forks in the road, try to lure the enemy vehicles co the opposite road you intend to take.</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>The rest is up to you! Good luck.</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr">&nbsp;</p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span><img src="https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/OcEPq5MgDgNbh2AM9uqNgCaJAaQuzxlU94SA4zH-Ugtg0wkD2Ji8pzjbLtm4FDOVngkhNYVN0r-nK_dGf3qRGjGucwInZ0h3_iJ5-9GKNmwGiJptk1-YAM3ETg1FGwt0u5f6DC8k" alt="" width="609" height="280" /></span></p>\n<p><span>&nbsp;</span></p>', 0, 0, 0, 'https://www.youtube.com/embed/h34MviiKXXc?ecver=1', 1),
(5, 'battleship-1993-nintendo', 'battleship 1993 nintendo', 'battleship', 'Game play invalves two basic operation: Positioning your warships for battle on the grid. Using weapons and strategy to destroy your enemy’s fleet before yours is destroyed!', '<h3 dir="ltr"><span>Starting the Game </span></h3>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>To start the game:</span></p>\n<ol>\n<li dir="ltr">\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Make sure your Nintendo Entertainment System {NES} is turned off.</span></p>\n</li>\n<li dir="ltr">\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Put the Battleship game in your NES.</span></p>\n</li>\n<li dir="ltr">\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Turn on the NES.</span></p>\n</li>\n<li dir="ltr">\n<p dir="ltr"><span>At the title screen, press </span><span>Start.</span></p>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Note: </span><span>To play with different levels an weapons, press </span><span>Select </span><span>to choose </span><span>Code</span><span>, then press </span><span>Start</span><span>. Use the Control Pad to enter the pass code, then press </span><span>Start</span><span>. See Pass Codes.</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span><img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/slcYH48gmazTQZ706zr4BhC5YzH7NIKJp6MnOhnYDmU21geE9T3UqHY_P8r3MHkyPEfJ0Sb5EsA9FZFCDi7loVmNpJrX7Z8UsCmCtCN0I4Mv4vhDdTPeGHPOwMm6SGHJdLMh8RBb" alt="" width="237" height="173" /></span></p>\n<h3 dir="ltr"><span>Game Controls</span></h3>\n<p dir="ltr"><span><img src="https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/vfVZCM65s9PQYi_LCHZ8YnpQRVt2Ajgm9xbFDGc3oSYTkpW7Rm5Ab9axct1dPmu3XTVcdfvo-5MWauHGvJ4H1ajRJXD2l4lwPDfUqDfMv9bh-GKNpMC42pnzppa1jRl8ck5zft8y" alt="" width="359" height="147" /></span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Control Pad:</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Press </span><span><img src="https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/DDkZxBkzwYkzmMpLqGmY9JGUP5JlVaHP6T6hEIGCAil5wMe5Hb8jSIP8kpHHCVwf-SFOCXN-V2rUvTOEGQL-K6WXs7ieqtreyVt8md5d5O-7E91V9H0GdgLmJkiUDWj3MCoGZnaS" alt="" width="68" height="20" /></span><span> to position the current ship or aim weapons on the grid.</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Buttons</span><span>:</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Start</span><span>Begin the game.</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Select</span><span>Pick a special weapon.</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>A</span><span>Place ships on the grid, accept the setup, and fire weapons.</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>B</span><span>Change ship orientation to harizontal or vertical on grid.</span></p>\n<p><span><span>&nbsp;</span></span></p>\n<h3 dir="ltr"><span>Playing the Game</span></h3>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Game play involves two basic operation:</span></p>\n<ol>\n<li dir="ltr">\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Positioning your warships for battle on the grid.</span></p>\n</li>\n<li dir="ltr">\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Using weapons and strategy to destroy your enemy&rsquo;s fleet before yours is destroyed!</span></p>\n</li>\n</ol>\n<h4 dir="ltr"><span>The Grid</span></h4>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>The </span><span>Battleship </span><span>grid is your battle field, twelve squares by eight squares.</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Use the grid to position your battle craft and to aim weapons at your opponent&rsquo;s vessels.</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span><img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/7Loj81q4ovf1NbkGx9MbnvV4rr4-qcZJTk331anAMKTmqXfADiEXVtClOMGMlbvkKWMoT0eG6-1KvO2ZZCUo_C1DWe9nNfKGhiNhnfid-oWN6B3gY0xy6IoQgY5Cs9BtvbEZLtvZ" alt="" width="425" height="151" /></span></p>\n<h4 dir="ltr"><span>Battle Craft</span></h4>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Before a battle, your ships appear, one by one, on the grid. Use the Control Pad to move them up, down, left, and right into position. Press </span><span>B </span><span>to rotate a ship from horizontal to vertical and back. Once you position a ship where you want it, press </span><span>A </span><span>to place it there.</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>After positioning your warships, you get a chance to reconsider your choices with a </span><span>Yes/No </span><span>box. Use the Control Pad to choose </span><span>No </span><span>and press </span><span>A </span><span>to start positioning over again. Choose </span><span>Yes </span><span>and press </span><span>A </span><span>to begin battle.</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span><img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/zVZ6eaNdVZTbr8GAN2p2CVRsQfIDX49Gbx33MAtAviHWWFkJNe3Oud70rM_MSAVAuViPi7sGkqDhNBeqTm2GfXNYembMQlckxcpUN6_wWAl_7FozqpBUb-8uBCX0kxTTjs6oT-_7" alt="" width="220" height="151" /></span></p>\n<h4 dir="ltr"><span>Battle Operations</span></h4>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Players take turns unleashing firepower on the opposing fleet. When it&rsquo;s your turn, your gun sights appear in the upper left square of the grid. Use your Control Pad to move the sights to the square on the grid that you want to target. Press </span><span>Select </span><span>to choose a special weapon and press </span><span>A </span><span>to fire.</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>A record of your shots appears on the grid as the game progresses. Blue circles are shots that missed, red circles are hits, and explasion icons show where you are hitting an enemy vessel. You must hit every square occupied by an enemy vessel to sink it. </span><span>D</span><span>uring your opponent&rsquo;s turn, you&rsquo;ll be able to watch as weaponry flies toward your ships. You&rsquo;ll also see the current state of your fleet on the grid.</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span><img src="https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/GlCgGFHfFa5V71RgSVULpzMfQ-EJxNzpxxaoJcSPEWKpC4mJrE7do1e0fWWPxEbDu4lmXZThFQMCVck2Lp9UmL-sbOmD8uweyv3J4DiRpRurcUXZDwc2_UBmorBjAcZphufr0ZEK" alt="" width="426" height="149" /></span></p>\n<h4 dir="ltr"><span>Stages and Levels</span></h4>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>The game </span><span>Battleship </span><span>has eight levels, each with five battles. You progress up the rank, and get new ships and or new weapons as shown.</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Level</span><span>Rank</span><span>Ships</span><span>Weapons</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>1</span><span>Lieutenant</span><span>Frigate</span><span>Polaris</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>D</span><span>estroyer</span><span>Asroc - 71</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Cruiser</span><span>Seadart</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Battleship</span><span>Tomahawk SSM</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>2</span><span>Lt. Commander</span><span>Same as Lieutenant, plus&hellip;</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Submarine</span><span>MK-48X</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>3</span><span>Commander</span><span>Same as Lt. Commander, plus&hellip;</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>D</span><span>estroyer</span><span>Asrac - 71</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Sonar</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>4 </span><span>Captain</span><span>Same as Commander, plus&hellip;</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Cruiser</span><span>Seadart</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Aerial Recon</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>5 </span><span>Rear Admiral </span><span>Same as Captain.</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>6</span><span>Vice Admiral </span><span>Same as Captain and </span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Rear Admiral, plus&hellip;</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Carrier</span><span>P-3 Orion</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>7</span><span>Admiral</span><span>Same as Vice Admiral, plus&hellip;</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Battleship</span><span>Tomahawk SSM</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Harpeon SSM</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>8</span><span>Fleet Admiral</span><span>Same as Admiral, plus&hellip;</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Carrier</span><span>P-3 Orion</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Talos</span></p>\n<p><span><span>&nbsp;</span></span></p>\n<h4 dir="ltr"><span>Weapons</span></h4>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>The standard missile on all ships is the RIM-64. You have an unlimited supply. In addition, depending on the level, you have a limited supply of special weapons.</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Weapon</span><span>Type of Ship</span><span>D</span><span>escription</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Palaris</span><span>Frigate</span><span>Four warheads that strike four different squares.</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Asroc - 71</span><span>D</span><span>estroyer</span><span>Also has four warheads, but fires a wider spread.</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Seadart</span><span>Cruiser</span><span>Five warhead missile.</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Tomahawk SSM</span><span>Battleship</span><span>Cruise missile that can strike six squares.</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>MK-48X</span><span>Submarine</span><span>Flying torpedo that hits five squares compocted.</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Harpoon</span><span>Battleship</span><span>Is equal to Tomahawk with a different &nbsp;pattem.</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Talos</span><span>Carriers</span><span>Fires on L-shaped pattem.</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Aerial Recon</span><span>Cruiser</span><span>Reconnaissance missions to detect enemies.</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Sonar</span><span>D</span><span>estroyer</span><span>An 8-square submarine sesor.</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>P-3 Orion</span><span>Carriers</span><span>A sub-hunter that can also altack other ships.</span></p>\n<p><span><span>&nbsp;</span></span></p>\n<h3 dir="ltr"><span>Pass Codes</span></h3>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>As you win each level, you get a four number password that lets you go directly to the next level from the start-up menu. It&rsquo;s a good idea to write own the passwords as you master each stoge, because they are hard to remember.</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>To begin play at an advanced level, choose </span><span>Code </span><span>on the </span><span>Battleship </span><span>game title screen, then press </span><span>Start</span><span>. Use the left and right Control Pad arrows to move the cursor left and right through the four spaces in the password. For each space, press the up and down Control Pad arrows to cycle through the numbers.</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>When you&rsquo;ve entered the password correctly, press </span><span>Start</span><span>.</span></p>\n<p><span><span>&nbsp;</span></span></p>\n<h3 dir="ltr"><span>Tips</span></h3>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Lay down a pattern</span><span>. A method for firing at enemy ships on the battle field helps. Remember how many squares your enemy&rsquo;s remaining battle craft occupy, and don&rsquo;t waste your fire power - and time - firing into random single squares that can&rsquo;t hold anything bigger than a submarine (unless that&rsquo;s what you&rsquo;re after).</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Use your extra firepower wisely</span><span>. You have a limited number of items providing extra firepower and tactical strength. Don&rsquo;t squander them all at the start of a battle. Each weapon is on board a particular vessel, so, when that vessel sinks, you lose the weapon. For example, if your battleship has taken four hits (one more and she goes down) and you haven&rsquo;t used your Tomahawk, put it into action immediately.</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Spread your ships apart.</span><span> Your enemy is very accurate, and has certain advantages. Keep your ships spread apart so that the enemy can only shoat one of your ships with the more powerful items.</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Keep your submarine separate. </span><span>The enemy tends to fire at squares next to one already shot. You can use this to your advantage. Position the submarine away from larger ships, and make your enemy take longer to find it.</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Reset if it looks too bad.</span><span> Remember you can always start each level over, if the enemy gets lucky on the first shots.</span></p>\n<p><span id="docs-internal-guid-53c09ff9-86cf-c949-d25b-4b5c236bc53f"><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /></span></p>', 0, 0, 0, 'https://www.youtube.com/embed/rReg5KDW6NM?ecver=1', 1);
INSERT INTO `game` (`id`, `url`, `name`, `name_vn`, `short_desc`, `long_desc`, `order_weight`, `is_promote`, `is_fearture`, `link_youtube`, `is_active`) VALUES
(6, 'bugs-bunny-crazy-castle-nintendo', 'bugs bunny crazy castle nintendo', 'bugs bunny crazy castle nintendo', 'Your goal is to complete all sixty levels by picking up all the carrots on each level. If you are successful in completing a level you receive an additional life.If you are captured by one of the rascals you lose a life and start the level over again.', '<h3 dir="ltr"><span>names of controller parts and operating instructions</span></h3>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>only controller 1 is used for this game.</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Control pas : use to move Bugs Bunny. Up and down directions are used to help Bugs climb stairs or enter pipes. Also used to enter password letter and to select from menus.</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Select button : used to pause the game.</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Start button &nbsp;: used to start the game and may also be used to pause the game during play.</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>A button : used to release the boxing glove at one of the rascals.</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>B button : same as a button.</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span><img src="https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/76A6C4ZCsceU_HyKrwrBKoc7_Oyq13qtlgobTDODIG1BFebF6CQs-XPcm0Wggks8TBnMNn3lz_jwEGHorFDsjXvgN3C_RCnenEbOwvZtehOlZIGXSiSbClcct8UlDFTD-hYN8h76" alt="" width="198" height="147" /></span></p>\n<h3 dir="ltr"><span>Objective</span></h3>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>You begin the game with 5 lives. Your goal is to complete all sixty levels by picking up all the carrots on each level. If you are successful in completing a level you receive an additional life.If you are captured by one of the rascals you lose a life and start the level over again. However, you can safely pass the rascals through doorways and pipes.If you lose all your lives , you are given a chance to continue the game from the current level. to do this use the control pad to highlight your choice and press the start button. otherwise you can start the game from first level.</span></p>\n<p><span><span>&nbsp;</span></span></p>\n<h3 dir="ltr"><span>controlling the bugs bunny</span></h3>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Bugs bunny is an agile character . it can even survive jumps from high places. You can use right and left on the control pad to move bins across the screen.</span></p>\n<p><span><span>&nbsp;</span></span></p>\n<h3 dir="ltr"><span>Climbing stairs </span></h3>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>You can use the up and down directions on the control pad to help Bugs Bunny climb up or down the stairs. Simply push up or down on the control pad when he is at the start of the stairs.</span></p>\n<p><span><span>&nbsp;</span></span></p>\n<h3 dir="ltr"><span>Using doorways</span></h3>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Many levels have doorways that lead up or down to other floors. To use these doorways push up or down on the control pad when bugs bunny is in front of the doorways.</span></p>\n<p><span><span>&nbsp;</span></span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span><img src="https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/K7MsM2-9R1OpWwZHgBFyF4EqT_-yjBE6M1vYPCIs2mDwrlBurNvuSGdNwM7PZB86iaDKY8D7jFI8-aYf8aoDQTBk_8nRVrqkIY7y9crvsUsIuyfixtZ-qAveKzneCvFhfY36ujQG" alt="" width="227" height="190" /></span></p>\n<h3 dir="ltr"><span>The pipes</span></h3>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>some levels contains a maze of pipes that Bugs Bunny can use to escape. To enter the pipes move to the entrance of the pipes and press up or down on the control pad. Bugs Bunny will appear at the other end of the pipes.</span></p>\n<p><span><span>&nbsp;</span></span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span><img src="https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/FzI-BQ3J-CU0ZSBJsc6Ruc2RqdEg2ryr4vLXsyHviChc4ejcSHs-M7IVOk7_jftybAQRdfzLWIiRj4NgxxgMq2zr8VkYL3CXEmiG_l4EjMEyJAWeO7arS703LfZzCs8Vu-EAefAT" alt="" width="245" height="200" /></span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Other items</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>There are number of other items in the castle that you should look for.</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Magic carrot juice: by drinking the magic carrot juice, Bugs bunny will become isvisible for short times.</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Boxing glove : if you pick up the boxing glove, you can use it to throw a punch at one of the rascals.Press A button and the glove will be thrown in the direction that Bugs Bunny is facing.</span></p>\n<p><span><span>&nbsp;</span></span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span><img src="https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/WSxd1xmZo-grkainckNCS8s-iEJ2fXSvjw9-UKx9NCqWNJGyz7nEolnLkVdomw4gLAu_-oVVAKOpW0ddXJk7IyzgoW9sxx4gl8AJd6y0QQqAPoi6Nye7bViZHOIa0KPV1aQ8FcAr" alt="" width="94" height="146" /></span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Safe, Wooden ,Crate, Bucket and 10tons weight: You can push one of these objects into the rascals of push if off a floor so the it falls down on one of them</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>The no carrot sign : on some levels you may encounter a no carrot sign. Be very careful. if you touch this sign you will be immediately forced to play a special level. if you succeed in clearing the level you will gain 3 lives. otherwise you will be forced back 3 levels.</span></p>\n<p><span><span>&nbsp;</span></span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>The rascals : daffy duck, sylvester , wiley coyote, yosemite sam</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span><img src="https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/YsvpywVsKNMY8ykdC32cA-rXrT4Jep88340GaNz4fKKEOKqiDvI2XhwehsmBtfpqRv_erW8LlkJj0TDXochmMxA1g9KkCNHkSN3gUheOjnXPHcbdBcigk35kDgbpUI1izKkgc1p5" alt="" width="614" height="469" /></span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span><img src="https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/WefE9bCzzNMIN83Ch0lxFN_rwkyf2xDQO9ZXagCpSORzX5rBU-O0fJI8aRJjQwa1Kz0SPHH_xzIQQmLGJtnNRniU-tBZ7G-6AkXjUFRaBDEtyuzNyZ_e39AMpRovv29TYeMOpBrH" alt="" width="587" height="456" /></span></p>\n<p><span>&nbsp;</span></p>', 0, 0, 0, 'https://www.youtube.com/embed/lC7FFkgtKkQ?ecver=1', 1),
(7, 'ninja-gaiden-tecmo-nintendo', 'ninja gaiden tecmo nintendo', 'ninja gaiden tecmo nintendo', 'The wind howls as the two Dueling Ninjas glare at each other in the moonlight. Though these men seem like little more than shadows in the air, the moonlight reveals just for an instant, a glint of light that proves to be the end of the contest.', '<h3 dir="ltr"><span>prologue </span></h3>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>The wind howls as the two Dueling Ninjas glare at each other in the moonlight. Though these men seem like little more than shadows in the air, the moonlight reveals just for an instant, a glint of light that proves to be the end of the contest. Ken, head of the Hayabusa clan which &nbsp;has for generations been the guardian of the Dragon sword, is defeated.</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Ken&rsquo;s son Ryu, after learning of his father&rsquo;s defeat find a letter. In it Ryu is told that if his father does not return, he must take the secret Dragon sword and go to America. Ryu senses danger awaiting him in America. What will be fate of Ninja Ryu?</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span><img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/Nrb3Pz1-VDOoCVws1VmCuYatD-_fu9N4iC943n6RSZ84cMMLDKrYDdfulDb9vdbyQ-nW6xtF9F8GJHsfL27eF-r985Jg0BMVvUM8FiFezqfRgstbgoUr7JhezTEwUuCPszRxCvdM" alt="" width="147" height="127" /></span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Run Ryu</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>This game is for one player only.</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Start button : start the game, become pause button when game is in play, press to skip cinema display.</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Select button : not use.</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Control cross : control the Ninja&rsquo;s direction</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Button A : jump the Ninja&rsquo;s direction</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Button B : control sword thrust</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>When you come to a ladder, use the control cross to climb up or down. Or you can jump on it. To jump down from the ladder, just press the opposite direction on the control cross and button A.</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span><img src="https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/6lPo7xvwU0KRVrqqeLs1Gqed-kTNQg1rhlaGxgNLIW3QPZRY29mHMH0o5VTkMr_HLkyirwtKyWGUkFo41pJbV6GEvU1OLcHkhVpNWgdFSuMG_BTY-xBniZM4OlZlhs7_bs79pUOB" alt="" width="270" height="111" /></span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span><img src="https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/imPlAN6USDpufPaOsQuY8141NukNyhXLRX-FPaRGdeuTxzweQAikXowZyHuU-daKMWOIsqG17vMwqFLOkQfcMFXx3GatVRI6Au_MAvWKOzZx02Bq1m1oeQ_ZrKHs_Ww5kDoTH1aO" alt="" width="221" height="135" /></span></p>\n<h3 dir="ltr"><span>Indicator display</span></h3>\n<p dir="ltr"><span><img src="https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/_akzJV929Nnv9PORYBSm3OfjknfQu5ghVt0rCCOLjWtm5femTHCbEV3J26CCNlRJML2jGGsa1cxjFYRWnCfGAVtvlZNTI8rH83fcvr7LEBK_Q03r-uq58-NX8QnZBsnz8gsxXfji" alt="" width="542" height="417" /></span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>1 Score display</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>2 Act level display</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>3 When time run down to 0, the game is over</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>4 When the number of lives becomes 0, the game is over</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>5 Spiritual Strength remaining</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>6 Collect the power item</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>7 Physical strength. You lose strength when wounded. When strength run down to 0 on life is lost </span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>8 Enemy Boss &rsquo;s strength. He loses strength when injured. When his strength runs down to 0 the enemy is destroyed.</span></p>\n<h3 dir="ltr"><span>THE ULTIMATE IN THE ART OF THE NINJA </span></h3>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Each stage has an item that needs to be collected to gain points, strength, weapons, etc.</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Spiritual strength : </span><span>Ryu has special powers when he uses this Spiritual strength. There are 2 kinds, red and blue, and you can increase your Spiritual strength by collecting them. Red is worth 10 points and blue 5 points.</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span><img src="https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/T9M5U1lvOwfndU__90OdHGdU7NFSQJhf2hTROlx7VrUhA59zaqlgm0m8rc9resZveAQrdxQtMDHC0SZeBpLmnY2_621GClHUkmMUKX9A56YBnJeYdl_elmskJhY8GAkiZWhPMLTr" alt="" width="102" height="91" /></span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Time freeze : </span><span>When Ryu collects one of these, everything on the screen can be frozen with the enemy and shots being frozen for 5 seconds.</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span><img src="https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/qY1IWGg47CXZBGVubEz-rweX2rh54aW71mstVNCm0kSLiB25cSanIl7qInFMF5SlRCQBYTF-n6HHl13wqLXBmT4Ex4xPA8Jy4U9BsorvyjVSW0Vu1brQ6WpQCnX67rMvzc7-qkrO" alt="" width="93" height="90" /></span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Bonus : </span><span>There are two kinds of bonuses, red and blue. You can increase your score by collecting the red one worth 1000 points and the blue 500 points.</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span><img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/5PbzmRb5CNs2Yyk-ibRR14HmNfa5A9MbExNkWTQqVE7v6aXo2_RX1UISMGsz4NxnaVQmMLUdRcMXq7K-H6mRujIac2yHt9QSFiCyfbJ8G6RWY6Q1JyaihpM7283heQ8r6F1LgYRM" alt="" width="89" height="87" /></span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Restoring physical strength</span><span> : when Ryu is injured in battle, strength is lost but this item will restore Ryu&rsquo;s energy level by six cells</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span><img src="https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/Q3Ub7DzaIFWRrJBsw0HblxoSuSjAh4EoAflnWRv2hIJ0fxKEHSFn6q0d0i31ue_4kk_SjGP4gRJymBbnQ68o4vWOGNRpTA9yRhgedbjLz5G7EEE9ooa6Axrzo5xTQZ5rDPbRge-j" alt="" width="94" height="91" /></span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>1 up</span><span> : collecting one of these will give you another life. This is one item you can&rsquo;t pass up</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span><img src="https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/Wkg_wrhtPBzGMAXELB0xkQ-CYHCzqHCzQX7BbIjk0KQRlVN-9nLnh6qocUHSmCc_erznJ1Oqoh_wvjl6nqkf4mVUalSGIgBAR4D6nfFnsnd4sTuxVHoiBizfbCj2Q87azlqCJYdu" alt="" width="94" height="90" /></span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Invincible fire-wheel</span><span>: when Ryu&rsquo;s anger turns to fire, this item has a flame circling around him at a super high speed, killing the enemy</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span><img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/WnsVcQ1mzyuxPItCelbstD6xX0BkOEp92dWISoUBnrrVnvw2jBGZrVzTJNpBXQ3r34wHu1RxsZopMj8QmDBcNZtfTUfJUxMjZ_L2wzG3JwUCYkUl2ejZdij8jsl8TJdo7sDwuH6O" alt="" width="89" height="88" /></span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Gained strength : increase your strength by collecting the following items. When you use these items the Spiritual Strength is used up. </span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Throwing star : in the spiritual world, this is considered a weak weapon, they only fly in a straight direction. </span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span><img src="https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/5bAOdirxpdHK9Lo5eBhGgOr8rtpi7w7c4YPevrVG8cOWs5-ebvKR57iPA7yjEh2Tt6y-DxbgHshqGbkAy_xcan_MFZS6VU0chlB2siwPAyJpWqxD-xsyVv5so3V4VGl81CBzqunH" alt="" width="93" height="92" /></span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Windmill throwing star: these stars cut right through the enemy and come back like a boomerang. Collect this one and cause some real damage to any enemy.</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span><img src="https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/ywd5tZTrAJwTwZe9jJ-zU5hbcTnVIUYTnffFyTJMKPqs8gWYODVtYreRUtYFhz8g0ewDy56102zdgHuWQHfdATPvToabf5HN-DBawBXnrqf0ToIglGWi7JHT1EKWG6llR6fSHYbT" alt="" width="90" height="92" /></span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>The art of the firewheel : Ryu discovered a secret art form at the end of a special training section. He takes 3 balls of fire and twirls them around, burning any enemy in its way.</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span><img src="https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/kkfreCMoaKvHLZy9JSsPrkZwHqxyrYzek5kLwIiaHUxUfkSDem6FXFI8_ecq8Qy57ComIq-F6piioNSMqs8qRNwIUlM4ts9SNXirw6NlyI_VOLGBbeF38DjwX8yfbiixicNB8y_Y" alt="" width="93" height="89" /></span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Jump &amp; slash technique : use this weapon in during a jump by pressing button B. You can jump and slash through the enemy. Only Ryu with his light and angle body can perform such a technique. This technique is especially handy when the enemy is below you.</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span><img src="https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/iNxlCeH4lfhacuDDobsyITrjwOgRTfL4yqNCayECLDmYqXVpo6fof23oIStMXYp1bBZP-GVAQNbcuYOqo3277Q918IV6a_Rw5MdlF7jQZZDuECRujiubYQxQUchvATN5X0o6QaWi" alt="" width="94" height="93" /></span></p>\n<p><span><span>&nbsp;</span></span></p>\n<h3 dir="ltr"><span>Act of the story''s progression ( 6 acts in all, 20 areas)</span></h3>\n<p><span><span>&nbsp;</span></span></p>\n<div dir="ltr">\n<table><colgroup><col width="*" /><col width="*" /><col width="*" /><col width="*" /><col width="*" /></colgroup>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>act\\area</span></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>1</span></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>2</span></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>3</span></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>4</span></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>act1 destiny</span></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>galesburg</span></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>jay''s bar</span></p>\n</td>\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>act2 the escape </span></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>outpost</span></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>death valley</span></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>amura ''s altar</span></p>\n</td>\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>act3 the chase</span></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>crystal lake</span></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>lizard mountains</span></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>yomi''s cave</span></p>\n</td>\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>act4 a trap</span></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>south american amazon</span></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir="ltr"><span> bazlisk mine gold</span></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>temple of darkness - hall of demons</span></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>space of kelberoos</span></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>act5 life or death combat</span></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>prison of the death</span></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>cliff</span></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>fast tower outer wall - the nails of lukifell</span></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>place of red execution</span></p>\n</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>act6 the fall of the demon</span></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>death bridge </span></p>\n</td>\n<td>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>temple of darkness - hall of judgement </span></p>\n</td>\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\n<td>&nbsp;</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n</div>\n<p><span><span><br /><br /></span></span></p>\n<h3 dir="ltr"><span>supply of power for the defeated </span></h3>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>If you have the will you continue even though you''ve lost all your lives, just press the start button and be on your way. You will begin your battle once again from the starting point of the &nbsp;area you were defeated.</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span><img src="https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/PXvqLy9cmf5jZIA45iHvI84Uoa7kITdJZoEcFWtRLXnX9doS2xjAMDqZEsDCBW9ujl20QRzq9lqruRLJgRwbAHPv9zyWtHymVVdik76XFdBhjI3DacFrEaHh9aSvk4CQolNR79Pd" alt="" width="385" height="46" /></span></p>\n<h3 dir="ltr"><span>Introduction of characters</span></h3>\n<p dir="ltr"><span><img src="https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/kjZJMS1gajVUJEQ8ls4EcbAy5IvDY0p6UHjEAoMH-uZEb9D_SSw6IQ6Ym_b1z5G-JIaP94UCkEmMxJSw3A42hc7c5hQwsgyjFrtbWy7OeMVcOBE9N4ajgTdX9xyOJ5-_wsKjiuK2" alt="" width="149" height="113" /></span><span>Ryu hayabusa</span><span> The hero . He was born into the ninja lineage of the Hayabusa Family. After he hears the news that his father was defeated in battle, he finds a letter his fallen father left behind. He obeys his father&rsquo;s will to go to American and take revenge on the enemy. But what will really become of him?</span></p>\n<p><span><span>&nbsp;</span></span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span><img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/MJe6_J8vM7IzGG7t4hEeVzV5FPJinXRuaMUqgnBO1ADHa1JN6bW-NNzqN5BI5GcptxBNslPMgbbgr0Mimf7sCblGKWBwcxgx_PJyJr9GznAZE6ZAM1jUHCmkI_-Iqqr0bR9bB2zb" alt="" width="131" height="108" /></span><span>Ken hayabusa </span><span>Ryu &rsquo;s father. &nbsp;Who he battle with and why de had a duel is still a mystery. Yet, although defeated, he left behind the secret Dragon sword and a letter for Ryu before leaving this world.</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span><img src="https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/zJ-0Gs1cZtWAb64fNLJIbjloaLS-gF-7oAewSUCKyGXhvJbP6FXDOBVWgIMHNskzr6bZxnhPKrpkXFjStmXkDYFybldUz4skUdphr6zYZnAKNrBOLRovX6h_NCfd5PIAw-wO5Dfx" alt="" width="129" height="107" /></span><span>Irene lew.</span><span> When Ryu arrives in America, he meetup with a mysterious woman in a bar. She has a tempting attractiveness about her. Nobody seems to know her name, nor anything about her.</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span><img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/mjSnRjV06M21vEY0aI4se76QNFlzRoxPBKyjbQ3bac3cO28jqTWliQ2gpHYcEfVMq6LEVVMzXdtmE0SaDb_N8_wOokAu3teKUuH1-iBzAEUA03s5FRdoGpsnEui84zhoxowJ08Cr" alt="" width="126" height="110" /></span><span>Walter smith</span><span> An archaeologist. During one of hist field trips, he was researching a mysterious sacred araed of some ruins. He discovered something that he had never seen before that looked evil. A discovery that turned a simple research trip into chaos.</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span><img src="https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/vmEa7ROlUWhu-XR0HcnN_oBT_JyP_kLLIzSZ21nlpVW33iPYEjMI3wTr9VMdtjxJKEutYISoViS3zSrjZdKH6cwSJ0Z1Kpv2APvUMx9P6XENF2B9umVyhkDcgXID6xQyTzxJDAGh" alt="" width="127" height="108" /></span><span>Foster</span><span> Although considered young in terms of age, he holds a powerful position in the Secret Auxiliary Unit of the CIA. he knows a lot of information &nbsp;about the whole episode which he tell Ryu and asks for his help.</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span><img src="https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/715mEXXRbl0MtAxdHABwgUnNyc0sjUDfha3W-pkqd0tc6tldeD0J7N8MAJo3UiketAgI8Zt2pVK08f95LaCD8zNMmwdV9hAN8TB4e-gs_6VJPyHvjdR6epes0LFpKRAe1BtPfdh7" alt="" width="128" height="104" /></span><span>Guardia de mieux(jaquio)</span><span> he calls himself JAQUIO. He is the almighty evil, determined to take over the world. He believes in the legend surrounds the evil temple at &nbsp;ruins. He has taken over the temple to build an empire of evil.</span></p>\n<p><span><span>&nbsp;</span></span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>&ldquo;The malice four&rdquo; are four evil forces hand picked by JAQUIO himself. The following is a description of the four evil forces and an evil spirit that has taken the form of creature called &ldquo;</span><span>Kelbeross</span><span>&rdquo;.</span></p>\n<p><span><span>&nbsp;</span></span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span><img src="https://lh5.googleusercontent.com/P-o-ZQ-Efwc5R_g8zcEYqp8aF1_9FibMctU8Ri0KgPI4Z9jIfjA5EgSD57JPIqjho0Yiwj-47KYGn0W2RZw2TUCB2b2Y5D0F_tHCfTifJeICE-LscDO8jrtwg50YxxI1wmBr9FW4" alt="" width="211" height="181" /></span><span>Barbarian</span><span> The boss of act 1. THe first of the malice four who will cut any thing to shreds that gets in it&rsquo;s way. Live in the deep forest of Brazil which he uses as his hideout. The natives are scared to death of this killer. Known as the &nbsp;executioner of South America. He attacks his enemy by ferociously swinging a huge ax.</span></p>\n<p><span><span>&nbsp;</span></span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span><img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/N7ICAo5I5M2yi-Ho9v3cmhwB6yypRl8gaQ_usHebSvxfUfedfPa465fYspfdY5i2BYK4rRLmt8jAigI-LEj8xY5Nx8KCpKlDKXhTLM7Kb_tsOcGCch0cV7VhjM30TUxPTA9jNa4-" alt="" width="171" height="218" /></span><span>Bomberhead</span><span> the boss of act 2. Deserted in the south Bronx, his life takes a big change for the worse. Presently, he controls the streets of New York with an iron fist as the Lord of Evil. An expert with sickle and chain, he wields it on his prey. The Bomberhead is the vice leader of &ldquo;the malice four&rdquo;. </span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span><img src="https://lh3.googleusercontent.com/3VL0o9S40vsA7VRudjdw3cLNNOdXfA9wLr7WlDOusY4hnalQNsMrV3RH6BQa2ypDdsjYs4aIC2fkMFYUR8eG_S662fXq8G90mY5lZXipXITmsvODI8xoFkuxux-kg0-v5jV6W6T6" alt="" width="170" height="222" /></span><span>Basaquer</span><span> the boss of act 3. Trained in china and master of all forms of the martial &nbsp;arts. He was a leader in a killers organization called the &ldquo;Five Ranges of Doom&rdquo;, but was expelled from the organization because he was too cruel. Just the type JAQUIO was looking for, Basaquer was chosen to be a member of &lsquo;The Malice Four&rsquo;</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span><img src="https://lh6.googleusercontent.com/2QAMK2FVKSDirzFBquqpOpxjuC2VQOGVLxW33mzssyD9C1s8dMk2GDu-43CL6lGichwosSqRWo-OomWIBv67Fz2ClMUurPMKNVcooPikI0VlyX_UffOQyHoofSPnjLvOR1VMzJbN" alt="" width="165" height="209" /></span><span>Kelbeross</span><span> The boss of act 4. Once the pet dog of JAQUIO. Kelberross was given up as a sacrifice victim for the evil spirits. As a result, the soul of Kelberross &nbsp;returns and takes the form of an evil creature as a loyal servant to protect JAQUIO</span></p>\n<p dir="ltr"><span><img src="https://lh4.googleusercontent.com/aRQS7llxcxsi0byyMR21CjvtLlIqI9o1LMIfqoxpFWyv8QrptDhxgkuzTJw0H5AriIp3PXwblZn2iV6U_45bFBbayL3GR4V9lnFQZ60cIutGutMLMU6LkmMqYYl6rWfwjeLMAdie" alt="" width="229" height="322" /></span><span>Bloody malth</span><span> &nbsp;the boss of the bosses. A North European legend that has been passed down from generation to generation about a cursed man with the &ldquo;Iron Mask of Blood&rdquo; and the &ldquo;Shield of Death&rdquo;. When he was young he studied Eastern Philosophy and became interested in Japanese martial arts. Now he seems to be invincible with the secret fighting techniques of the Orient.</span></p>\n<p><span><span>&nbsp;</span></span></p>\n<h3 dir="ltr"><span>Epilogue</span></h3>\n<p dir="ltr"><span>Cinema action &ldquo;Ninja Gaiden&rdquo; is depending on your skills to save the world. Can you do it? Is is essential that you succeed. Awaiting you is an ending that you just have to experience for yourself. May the spirit of the Dragon be with you.</span></p>\n<p><span>&nbsp;</span></p>', 0, 0, 0, 'https://www.youtube.com/embed/ueeKMQSS4bw?ecver=1', 1);

